oK1fGumG4tpacKJqdgtiL3thwbR47BoLKi0ROcxMO-l4abhEDxIiVDWzJt5Gkn925Pj6gCTRvPUMIGZxDS2TxewoEGclNLdxf2KzxM7Q0k_oFrChle5Eyy-fPB-TACIo7K4J_UiLnDkZhqG9KowIaE8_9rGy9bTT9u5-uEjmalITKG9ViAsJOPzwgn6QEfXX91KFw5vQQkrNxbkAjocOIDwsg==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Ensuring route completion**\\n\\nI need to ensure that the route completes before making any assertions since it’s synchronous. It seems like a top-level public class is currently public, which is fine, but existing test methods are package-private. I should definitely edit those to make sure everything is correct and accessible. It's important to have everything structured properly for effective testing—I'm refining this to keep things seamless!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_jU4ytGie1QyTVw8QK0fhMl4V|fc_08c11294fc62190e0169fd2bb9af608197b7728890096aca6e", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.camel/camel-core-engine/4.19.0/src/test/java/org_apache_camel/camel_core_engine/Camel_core_engineTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    @Test\n    void routeTemplatesMaterializeRunnableRoutesBeforeStartup() throws Exception {\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void contentBasedRouterSendsMessagesToMatchingBranch() throws Exception {\n        DefaultCamelContext context = new DefaultCamelContext();\n        try {\n            context.addComponent(\"memory\", new InMemoryComponent());\n            context.addRoutes(new RouteBuilder() {\n                @Override\n                public void configure() {\n                    from(\"memory:orders\")\n                            .routeId(\"priority-router\")\n                            .choice()\n                                .when(header(\"priority\").isEqualTo(\"gold\"))\n                                    .setHeader(\"tier\", constant(\"premium\"))\n                                    .to(\"memory:premium\")\n                                .otherwise()\n                                    .setHeader(\"tier\", constant(\"stand